Diagram 1 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Did you find white 1?
\par
\par Making an eye like this is a clever move.
\par
\par If black plays at B2, white pokes out black's eye with 3 and the situation becomes an eye vs. no eye capturing race.
\par .
\par Instead of playing 2, if black plays at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white will still play 3.
\par
\par
\par }
