Diagram 2 (Variation)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In response to white \'a1\'e2, if black plays at 1, white crosses under with 2 and that's it.
\par
\par Black cannot separate white due to self-dansu.
\par
\par Instead of 2, white can also play at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par
\par Black's shape does not look easy to kill, but white's single blow at \'a1\'e2 takes away black's way to live.
\par }
